<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1904,2039]" pageId="17" pageNumber="374">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Park, 2008" authorityName="Park" authorityYear="2008" box="[280,553,1904,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Pectinimura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,418,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="374">Pectinimura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; Byun, B. - K." box="[428,553,1904,1931]" pageId="17" pageNumber="374" pagination="110 - 115" refId="ref9930" refString="Park, K. - T. &amp; Byun, B. - K. (2008) A new genus Pectinimura (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea, Lecithoceridae), with four new species from Thailand and the Philippines. Florida Entomologist, 91 (1), 110 - 115. https: // doi. org / 10.1653 / 0015 - 4040 (2008) 091 [0110: ANGPLG] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2008">Park, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the related genus to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Herrich-Schaffer, 1853" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1853" box="[1032,1436,1904,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Lecithocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1166,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="374">Lecithocera</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer, 1853
</taxonomicName>
belonging to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[459,625,1940,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lecithocerinae">Lecithocerinae</taxonomicName>
and comprises 13 known species: four species from the 
<collectingRegion box="[1257,1436,1940,1966]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="17" pageNumber="374">Oriental Region</collectingRegion>
and nine species from the Oceanian Region. The genus is characterized by the male genitalia with comb-like plate on the valva. This is the first species reported from the Afrotropical Region.
</paragraph>
